Brute Force : T.C. - O(N), S.C. - O(N)
Approach : Plus minus and making use of array in terms of indexing helps. Here removeIndex helps in answering.

class Solution:
    def removeNthFromEnd(self, head: Optional[ListNode], n: int) -> Optional[ListNode]:
        nodes = []
        curr = head

        while curr:
            nodes.append(curr)
            curr = curr.next

        removeIndex = len(nodes) - n

        if removeIndex == 0:
            return head.next

        nodes[removeIndex - 1].next = nodes[removeIndex].next

        return head

Optimal Iterative Solution : T.C. - O(N), S.C. - O(1)
Approach : The array was taking extra space in the above solution, and we needed only N (len(arr)), so took that only.
class Solution:
    def removeNthFromEnd(self, head: Optional[ListNode], n: int) -> Optional[ListNode]:
        N = 0
        curr = head

        while curr:
            N += 1
            curr = curr.next

        removeIndex = N - n

        if removeIndex == 0:
            return head.next

        curr = head

        for i in range(N - 1):
            if (i+1) == removeIndex:
                curr.next = curr.next.next
                break
            curr = curr.next
        return head
                
